input: Country: France. Purchaser Name: COMMUNITY OF COMMUNITIES OF TERNOIS. Summary: Supply of Non-School Books for the Media Library of the Third Lieu Cultural of Saint-Pol-Sur-Ternoise. Description: Located in Pas-de-Calais, the Community of Communes of Ternois, TernoisCom (103 municipalities 38,000 inhabitants) has assumed responsibility for public reading facilities inherited from the former intercommunal authorities since 2017, the date of its creation. Among the main structuring towns of the territory, Saint-Pol-sur-Ternoise, the largest, does not yet have public reading facilities but only a library from the Bibliotheque Pour Tous associative network. This absence means that a significant part of the territory's population is not served today. In response To meet this need, TernoisCom is currently carrying out the project of creating very comprehensive equipment in Saint-Pol-sur-Ternoise, combining multiple other uses relating to culture, digital technology and leisure around books and reading. The objective of this hybridization is to increase the frequentation of the place and to put in contact with a cultural offer populations who would not have spontaneously walked through the door of a media library but will, in this place, be attracted by other uses to then discover what a media library is today, far from the dusty model of silent libraries of yesteryear. The subject of the consultation concerns the supply of non-school books for the constitution of the starting fund of the media library of the cultural third place of Saint-Pol-sur-Ternoise.. Published Date: 2025-11-07. Closing Date: 2025-12-11. Competition: ICB. Financier Name: Self Financed

Description: The purpose of this consultation is the maintenance of all video protection installations deployed by the city of Pornic in certain public spaces located in the municipality. The aim is to conclude a single-award framework agreement to be implemented as vouchers are issued. order concerning services relating to the maintenance of all video protection installations deployed by the city of Pornic. Maintenance includes all measures intended to preserve the reference state of the video protection installations deployed in the City and materials contributing to the operation of this device. It includes, in a first theme, technical inspections and maintenance operations (preventive maintenance) and repairs (corrective maintenance) whose aim is to: protect the installation against damage due to to the use and action of time; repair any damage that occurs; ensure all the functions for which they are intended. It also includes for a second theme, additional modernization work, the supply and implementation of management of the computer-assisted maintenance, all with the aim of optimizing the overall maintenance and efficiency of the video protection ecosystem..
